translated: Biörnerud, Lars Tage Nils, director, Gothenburg, b. August 13th, 1908 in Landvetter, Gothenburg and Bohus County. 1st marriage in 1935 with Elsa Biörnerud. Children: Ingela b. 1938, Ylva b. 1943, Lars b. 1944. Education: graduated from Borås high school in 1928, completed vocational course for students at Gothenburg's School of Commerce in 1930. Correspondent at A-B C. Fr. Wærn & Co. in Gothenburg from 1930 to 1934, department head at O. Chr. Oisen & Co. A-B in Gothenburg from 1934 to 1940, pro-curator at Nils Troèdsson &amp; Co. A-B in Gothenburg since 1940, director at Nils Troèdsson Paper Co A-B in Gothenburg since 1944. Also serves as a supplementary member in the board of directors for the latter mentioned company since 1944, as well as a supplementary member in the board of directors for the Swedish Transmarine Export Association.
